n to a test-local `ConfiguredMD5` subclass before calling `HostKey.getFingerPrint(new JSch())`.\n- This forces `HostKey.getFingerPrint` to execute its configurable reflection path:\n  - `Class.forName(jsch.getConfig(\"md5\"))`\n  - `Class#newInstance()`\n- The test restores the default `com.jcraft.jsch.jce.MD5` config afterward.\n- It still verifies supported behavior by checking the returned host key fingerprint against an independently computed MD5 fingerprint.\n\nTests were not run, per instruction.", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_00673fc4932446e7016a11111cbe5481979bdb088e5ce55a10\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1134, "output": 805, "cacheRead": 27648, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 29587, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1779503377009, "responseId": "resp_00673fc4932446e7016a1111119dac81978ed8073d39aaa3c7"}}
